sing WordPress&#8217;s mechanism for version-ed cacheing of resources (which is why not everybody was seeing the mess), but for some reason, these customers&#8217; setups appear to be cacheing things they shouldn&#8217;t. This release overcomes that, and removes the need to hit &#8220;Reload&#8221; in your web browser for affected users.</p>\n<p>The second issue affects downloads of large zips made through the dashboard. Some webservers were failing to deliver these, related to an incidental change in re-factored code in this area of UpdraftPlus. This is now also avoided in the new release.</p>\n<p>David Anderson (lead developer, UpdraftPlus)</p>\n<span class="et_bloom_bottom_trigger"></span><p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-1-11-26-free-version-2-11-26-paid-versions/">UpdraftPlus 1.11.26 (free version) / 2.11.26 (paid versions)</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://updraftplus.com">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href="http://updraftplus.com">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:84:"https://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-1-11-26-free-version-2-11-26-paid-versions/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:79:"https://updraftplus.com/updraftplus-1-11-26-free-version-2-11-26-paid-versions/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n		