;s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:33:"https://updraftplus.com/?p=142229";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:744:"<p>Short version: 1) Copy.Com will be closing their doors in 3 months time. 2) Choose a different cloud storage provider for your backups! 3) We&#8217;re sad, but can&#8217;t do anything about it, or answer questions about Copy.Com&#8217;s decisions &#8211; we&#8217;re &#8230; <a href="https://updraftplus.com/barracuda-are-end-of-lifing-copy-com/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://updraftplus.com/barracuda-are-end-of-lifing-copy-com/">Barracuda are end-of-lifing Copy.Com</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://updraftplus.com">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href="http://updraftplus.com">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"udadmin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2205:"<p><strong>Short version:</strong> 1) Copy.Com will be closing their doors in 3 months time. 2) Choose a different cloud storage provider for your backups! 3) We&#8217;re sad, but can&#8217;t do anything about it, or answer questions about Copy.Com&#8217;s decisions &#8211; we&#8217;re just the messenger!</p>\n<p><strong>Long version</strong></p>\n<p>In case you&#8217;ve not heard&#8230; from May 1st, Copy.Com storage with be no more. Copy.Com&#8217;s parent company, Barracuda, have decided to close down their product.</p>\n<p>Relevant links:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="https://blog.barracuda.com/2016/02/01/message-from-gm-of-storage/">Blog announcement</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://techlib.barracuda.com/Copy/EndOfLife">Documentation, including links to FAQs</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>From our point of view, this is a pity &#8211; Copy.Com has always been a reliable service, and was one of the nicest one to code for, having decent documentation and an intuitive interface; though, Copy.Com didn&#8217;t do that much to keep their software development kit up-to-date with fixes and improvements (but, on the other hand, it basically just worked). But, such is life &#8211; and there have been signs for a while that the big four &#8211; Dropbox, Amazon, Google, Microsoft &#8211; were consolidating their grip. (Which is why UpdraftPlus has added support for OneDrive, Azure Blob Storage, and Google Cloud in the last year, on top of its existing support for Dropbox, Google Drive and AWS).</p>\n<p>So, if you were using the Copy.Com module in UpdraftPlus to store your backups, then you&#8217;ll want to change to a different solution in the next 3 months. <a href="https://updraftplus.com/shop/updraftplus-premium/">Thankfully, UpdraftPlus Premium has lots to choose from!</a></p>\n<p>David Anderson (lead developer, UpdraftPlus)</p>\n<span class="et_bloom_bottom_trigger"></span><p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://updraftplus.com/barracuda-are-end-of-lifing-copy-com/">Barracuda are end-of-lifing Copy.Com</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://updraftplus.com">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href="http://updraftplus.com">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:66:"https://updraftplus.com/barracuda-are-end-of-lifing-copy-com/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_exp